reviews.content:
@Nebraska - Art Director not approved.

The film is about an aging man who goes on a road trip with his estranged son to claim a $1 million sweepstake prize.

Like the state itself, the film is forgettable with dialogue as flat as the landscape. The black and white treatment only compounds the bleakness of a senior moment. A sad reminder of the slow march of time towards frailty. A highlight in this snoozer is June Scuibb's ballsy performance. I may have enjoyed her more if I hadn't slept through parts of the film.
